column2: Lake levels too low to get boat in water in September.
Need Rain! Lake's getting so low it's getting near impossible to launch the boat.
Over the last 10 days we've gotten 6" of needed rain. Need at least another 6-8" to bring lake levels up to where they should be.
The 6" of rain we got earlier in the month has all but evaporated away. The boat is again resting on the lake bottom when next to the pier.
Where is our rain It's all going south of us. We are down over 12" by now.
Couldn't ask for a nicer fall day. Makes one glad he's retired and able to be outside to enjoy it.
Almost got caught in a whirlwind that suddenly moved out from the shore and  into the lake. After heading directly toward us for a while it suddenly changed directions and moved away.
What's with all this wind this year  Making it hard to do testing on a scheduled bases.
Lake's getting as low as it was last year. May not be able to get boat in water to do any August tests if we don't get lots of rain.
As low as our lake is again this year I probably wouldn't be able to get the boat off of shore to do any further lake monitoring.
Air temperature 77 degrees.  Sunny blue sky. Water levels historically high- with shoreline flooding. Water shield present. pH not done.
